rely a number of businesses, who's purpose in life is to make money for their owners and stockholders. revenues come largely from advertisers who merely want maximum useful exposure per dollar. the media is like fast food; the quality of the food (or of the reporting) will improve only if the customers demand as such. otherwise, it is business as usual. -- mark walsh (walsh@optilink) -- uucp: uunet!optilink!walsh amateur radio: km6xu@wx3k -- aol: bigcookie@aol.com -- uscf: l10861 "what, me worry?" - william m. gaines, 1922-1992 "i'm gonna crush you!" - andre the giant, 1946-1993
